cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.IR, cs.SE, cs.PL 

This paper discusses the benefits and limitations of column stores in data warehousing applications and proposes ways to incorporate these benefits into traditional relational engines. Therefore, it is most likely to belong to the Database (cs.DB) and Data Structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. It also discusses query optimization and performance improvement, which are relevant to Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper proposes a simulation approach to incorporate C-store benefits into traditional engines, which is related to Programming Languages (cs.PL).
